WEBVTT

00:01.069 --> 00:03.537
Previously on This Is Us...

00:03.571 --> 00:05.473
I came here for my brother.

00:05.506 --> 00:07.041
I was hoping
to take him back with me.

00:07.075 --> 00:09.543
You should've left me to rot!

00:09.577 --> 00:11.079
Join my campaign.

00:11.112 --> 00:13.081
You swear this is not
a pity job?

00:13.114 --> 00:16.050
I wouldn't dare
offer you a pity job.

00:16.084 --> 00:18.152
-Hey, I'm Randall.
-Uh, Jesse.

00:18.186 --> 00:19.820
RANDALL:
Nice to meet you, Jesse.

00:19.853 --> 00:21.089
Did William
ever mention a Jesse?

00:21.122 --> 00:23.091
Dad, Grandpa's gay.

00:23.124 --> 00:26.026
Or at least bi.

00:26.060 --> 00:28.762
There's no Jack here.
It's Pilgrim Rick.

00:28.796 --> 00:31.665
YOUNG RANDALL:
I want every Thanksgiving

00:31.699 --> 00:34.268
to be like this
for the rest of my life.

00:44.545 --> 00:46.280
:
Can I help you with anything?

00:46.314 --> 00:48.015
Maybe you could have asked me
that question

00:48.048 --> 00:49.950
before I started
cutting the onions.

00:49.983 --> 00:52.186
No, because then you'd
have me cutting the onions.

00:52.220 --> 00:53.387
Yeah.

00:55.789 --> 00:57.191
This is probably
our last Thanksgiving

00:57.225 --> 00:58.792
with the kids all living here.

00:58.826 --> 01:00.628
Yeah, well, with how much
they've been

01:00.661 --> 01:02.796
at each other's throats,
maybe that's a good thing.

01:02.830 --> 01:04.798
-Whoa, Bec.

01:04.832 --> 01:07.201
Are you opening up a pie shop
that I don't know about?

01:07.235 --> 01:09.303
I know,
I kind of overdid it, huh?

01:11.439 --> 01:14.242
Do you think we made a mistake
by not giving the kids

01:14.275 --> 01:17.245
some big,
extended family Thanksgiving?

01:17.278 --> 01:19.447
No, come on.
Our families are terrible.

01:19.480 --> 01:21.149
But Miguel's coming over.

01:21.182 --> 01:22.783
He's pretty much
extended family.

01:22.816 --> 01:25.219
I know, and I feel like
a traitor for having him over.

01:25.253 --> 01:26.620
Bec, you're not a traitor.

01:26.654 --> 01:28.156
His ex is my best friend,

01:28.189 --> 01:29.823
and he's coming
for Thanksgiving.

01:29.857 --> 01:31.759
That's best friend treason.

01:31.792 --> 01:34.995
Bec, it's the man's first
Thanksgiving since the divorce.

01:35.028 --> 01:37.898
And with Shelly taking the kids
to Connecticut for her family,

01:37.931 --> 01:39.500
he would be alone otherwise.

01:39.533 --> 01:42.503
Well, maybe he wouldn't be alone

01:42.536 --> 01:44.972
if he'd fought a little harder
to save his marriage.

01:45.005 --> 01:46.974
That is Shelly's side of things.

01:47.007 --> 01:48.842
I didn't know
we were taking sides.

01:48.876 --> 01:50.944
Well, do you want to take sides?

01:50.978 --> 01:52.313
I don't want to take sides.
I don't want to have a fight.

01:52.346 --> 01:53.614
I don't want
to take sides, either.

01:56.517 --> 01:57.918
What is that?

01:57.951 --> 02:00.087
Uh... sounds like laughter.

02:00.120 --> 02:02.089
-It couldn't be.

02:02.122 --> 02:05.125
Shall we ever.

02:08.162 --> 02:10.130
:
Don't make it complicated.

02:10.164 --> 02:12.433
-Randall's college essay.

02:12.466 --> 02:14.101
-It's not that funny.
-KATE: Okay, then go ahead.

02:14.134 --> 02:15.336
-Read them the question.
-No.

02:15.369 --> 02:17.338
-Read it.
-Come on.

02:17.371 --> 02:18.872
-JACK: Come on.
-So the question is,

02:18.906 --> 02:22.109
"So far, what person has
most impacted your life?"

02:22.142 --> 02:23.677
And he doesn't want to go

02:23.711 --> 02:25.613
with the firefighter
who found him on the steps.

02:25.646 --> 02:27.215
-RANDALL:
But the question is flawed.
-KATE: No, no, no.

02:27.248 --> 02:28.949
The question
is an underhanded softball

02:28.982 --> 02:30.518
-that you should clobber.
-Clobber, Randall.

02:30.551 --> 02:32.019
-No...
-It's so easy.

02:32.052 --> 02:33.821
The whole premise
of the question is wrong.

02:33.854 --> 02:35.556
No one person can
have the greatest impact

02:35.589 --> 02:37.625
-on your life.
-Oh, my-- Blah, blah, blah.

02:37.658 --> 02:39.393
Can someone please tell him
that he's overthinking this?

02:39.427 --> 02:41.061
Hey, your brother's gonna
make the right decision.

02:41.094 --> 02:42.396
What do you think?

02:42.430 --> 02:44.532
The fireman's a layup.

02:44.565 --> 02:46.400
-Oh! There you go.
-He said it himself.
-Oh...

02:46.434 --> 02:48.135
-Come on.
-Kev, ball.

02:48.168 --> 02:49.303
-Bah.
-Interception!
-REBECCA: Not inside...

02:51.439 --> 02:53.407
*

02:53.441 --> 02:55.676
-Whoa!
-I don't want to play.

02:55.709 --> 02:58.212
I'm not playing!

02:58.246 --> 03:00.080
-RANDALL: Touchdown!

03:00.113 --> 03:01.682
Doorbell. Doorbell.

03:01.715 --> 03:03.717
Hey, Kev, you want to get that?

03:03.751 --> 03:05.986
-KATE: Oh!
-RANDALL: Oh!

03:06.019 --> 03:08.322
How long does it take them
to go to the store

03:08.356 --> 03:10.858
and get cranberry sauce?
I called an hour ago, Shelly.

03:12.693 --> 03:16.564
Shelly, I just want to say
happy Thanksgiving to our kids.

03:16.597 --> 03:18.599
Shelly, don't hang up on...

03:18.632 --> 03:21.602
She hung up on me.

03:21.635 --> 03:23.371
Hey.

03:23.404 --> 03:26.374
Hey. Happy Thanksgiving.

03:26.407 --> 03:28.141
I brought a pie.

03:30.311 --> 03:32.246
-REBECCA: I'm gonna go put it
in the kitchen.
-Yeah, okay.

03:34.948 --> 03:36.884
*

03:41.755 --> 03:43.724
So, the person who's made
the biggest impact on your life?

03:43.757 --> 03:45.459
-Yeah.
-Ooh, that fireman
who found you.

03:45.493 --> 03:46.894
-No. No. I'm not...
-Colleges love
that kind of stuff.

03:46.927 --> 03:48.562
-I'm not doing that...
-Hello.

03:48.596 --> 03:50.564
Uh, can somebody grab
the Pilgrim Rick hat, please?

03:50.598 --> 03:52.232
Wow. You guys
still do that stuff?

03:52.266 --> 03:53.634
Sure do, pal. Family tradition.

03:53.667 --> 03:55.536
-That we've outgrown.
-Oh, come on.

03:55.569 --> 03:57.771
Aw, I still like when Dad
does Pilgrim Rick.

03:57.805 --> 03:59.072
Thank you, Katie girl.

03:59.106 --> 04:00.107
Yeah, and it covers
all the grays.

04:00.140 --> 04:01.542
-ALL: Oh!
-Whoa!

04:01.575 --> 04:03.444
Ooh, do you need some ice
for that burn?

04:03.477 --> 04:05.546
-She got you.
-I thought this was
a Thanksgiving dinner.

04:05.579 --> 04:06.780
I didn't realize it was a roast.

04:06.814 --> 04:08.382
KATE:
Hey, a little bit of both.

04:08.416 --> 04:09.483
-JACK: Yeah, okay, sure.
-Here, you might need the...

04:10.851 --> 04:12.920
JACK:
You knock it off with that...

04:12.953 --> 04:15.088
Excuse me a second.

04:15.122 --> 04:16.657
RANDALL:
Don't take sides.

04:24.131 --> 04:26.634
Hey. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

04:29.169 --> 04:32.973
You know, I get the stress
of who gets the house,

04:33.006 --> 04:35.809
and the alimony
and all that crap,

04:35.843 --> 04:38.912
but turning the kids against me?

04:38.946 --> 04:41.449
Your kids can't be turned
against you, Miguel.

04:41.482 --> 04:42.850
Okay? They love you.

04:42.883 --> 04:45.152
Come on, Jack.
Just say it like it is.

04:45.185 --> 04:47.187
We both know that I wasn't there

04:47.220 --> 04:49.423
for Andy and Amber
like I should've been.

04:49.457 --> 04:52.826
Work always came first,
and now I'm paying the price.

04:55.663 --> 04:58.466
Okay, fine.

04:58.499 --> 05:02.436
You could have... you could've
been a more present father.

05:02.470 --> 05:06.640
You know? But you wanted
to provide for your family.

05:06.674 --> 05:10.010
I've never seen anyone work
as hard as you.

05:10.043 --> 05:13.881
You know, I remember, I remember
when you made upper management.

05:13.914 --> 05:17.551
I remember how proud of you
I was.

05:17.585 --> 05:21.489
You were gonna be doing
the big deals with the big boys.

05:21.522 --> 05:24.625
And then you figured out
that the big deals

05:24.658 --> 05:26.627
were done on a golf course.

05:26.660 --> 05:28.629
And so what did you do?

05:28.662 --> 05:31.732
You bought some clubs,
you got lessons.

05:31.765 --> 05:34.301
You would go to the range
after work and hit balls...

05:34.334 --> 05:36.404
Instead of going home
and having a family dinner.

05:36.437 --> 05:38.472
...until a Puerto Rican kid

05:38.506 --> 05:40.708
who'd never been
to business school,

05:40.741 --> 05:44.378
who-who'd never set foot
on a golf course,

05:44.412 --> 05:49.316
let alone played on one, joins
his boss's Saturday foursome,

05:49.349 --> 05:53.153
and he becomes country club
champion four years in a row.

05:53.186 --> 05:55.556
You got to take that fight,

05:55.589 --> 06:00.894
and you need to show your kids
that you are still their father.

06:00.928 --> 06:03.831
You hear me?

06:03.864 --> 06:05.833
Yeah.

06:05.866 --> 06:10.538
You don't want to be 65 years
old and not know your grandkids.

06:19.212 --> 06:22.382
Man, what's a guy got to do
to get some turkey around here?

06:29.790 --> 06:31.525
Hey, have you heard
from Jae

06:31.559 --> 06:34.094
-About moving today's
soup kitchen visit

06:34.127 --> 06:35.463
from the church
to the rec center.

06:35.496 --> 06:36.764
:
Not yet. What about it?

06:36.797 --> 06:37.865
Can you rinse and repeat, baby?

06:37.898 --> 06:38.866
I'm sorry.

06:43.270 --> 06:45.906
-Ah...

06:45.939 --> 06:48.476
-I have not heard from Jae-won.
-Okay.

06:48.509 --> 06:50.478
I hope he's on board with me
changing the venue.

06:50.511 --> 06:52.813
I'm not sure he likes me
working on the campaign.

06:52.846 --> 06:54.815
What? That's crazy.

06:54.848 --> 06:56.450
You've had, like,
300 stupendous ideas

06:56.484 --> 06:57.651
since joining my campaign.

06:57.685 --> 06:59.419
The fish-fry fundraiser,

06:59.453 --> 07:01.321
pushing for the town hall debate
next week.

07:01.354 --> 07:03.323
Plus, you look smoking
even when you're dressing down

07:03.356 --> 07:04.958
for a soup kitchen.

07:04.992 --> 07:06.426
Okay. You're right.

07:06.460 --> 07:07.795
I'm crushing being
your field director.

07:07.828 --> 07:08.996
You are.

07:09.029 --> 07:11.398
-Mm.

07:11.431 --> 07:13.467
-Mm-mm.

07:13.501 --> 07:14.502
-Hustle now.

07:14.535 --> 07:15.603
-Yes.
I'll meet you downstairs.

07:15.636 --> 07:17.571
Toby and Kate will be here
any minute.

07:17.605 --> 07:20.474
You sure they're up to cooking
while we're out?

07:20.508 --> 07:22.275
I mean, Kate's all IVF'd up,

07:22.309 --> 07:23.744
and Toby's just getting back
on his feet.

07:23.777 --> 07:25.112
I quadruple-checked.

07:25.145 --> 07:26.446
They are excited
to be in charge this year.

07:26.480 --> 07:27.548
TESS:
Mom?

07:29.316 --> 07:31.184
Yeah?

07:42.863 --> 07:45.533
-TESS: I don't feel good.

07:45.566 --> 07:47.801
Hmm.

07:47.835 --> 07:50.604
No fever. Go lie down, okay?

07:50.638 --> 07:53.507
-I'll tell Aunt Kate
to keep an eye on you.
-Okay.

07:53.541 --> 07:56.376
*

07:58.746 --> 08:00.881
Happy Thanksgiving.

08:00.914 --> 08:02.282
-Happy Thanksgiving.
-Happy Thanksgiving.

08:02.315 --> 08:03.951
The cavalry is here!

08:03.984 --> 08:06.987
All right. What do we got here?

08:07.020 --> 08:09.322
-Hey-oh.
-Hi.

08:09.356 --> 08:12.325
How's my sis feeling with her
little turducken in the oven?

08:12.359 --> 08:13.627
-Pretty good.

08:13.661 --> 08:15.362
Yeah. The morning sickness
isn't too bad,

08:15.395 --> 08:17.665
and Toby's been coming through
with the back rubs.

08:17.698 --> 08:19.567
Yeah. My fingers are basically
tension assassins.

08:19.600 --> 08:21.735
-Give me some of that. Uh.

08:21.769 --> 08:23.370
Tess isn't feeling well.

08:23.403 --> 08:25.372
Is it okay with you guys
if she stays here with you?

08:25.405 --> 08:26.840
Yeah, that'd be
good practice for us

08:26.874 --> 08:28.876
for when we have
a little sicko of our own.

08:28.909 --> 08:31.178
-If this is too much
for you, Tobe, you just...

08:31.211 --> 08:32.546
Because we can make another
arrangement, right?

08:32.580 --> 08:34.481
Look, guys, guys, guys, guys.
Hey, this-- it's great.

08:34.514 --> 08:36.216
We'll watch Tess.
This is gonna be fine.

08:36.249 --> 08:39.152
Look, my comeback is about
small victories, all right?

08:39.186 --> 08:42.189
And helping Kate cook
a 15-pound Butterball

08:42.222 --> 08:43.924
using Snoop and Martha's recipe

08:43.957 --> 08:46.259
will be a small
but meaningful victory.

08:46.293 --> 08:48.061
RANDALL:
All right, then.

08:48.095 --> 08:50.831
Hey, girls, let's hit the road!

08:50.864 --> 08:52.265
BETH:
So, if anything happens,

08:52.299 --> 08:54.034
just give us a call.
We'll be back by 4:00.

08:54.067 --> 08:55.703
-Yep.
-Okay.
All right. Let's hit it.

08:55.736 --> 08:57.838
Hey, Annie, why is there
a gigantic teddy bear

08:57.871 --> 08:59.106
sitting at
the dining room table?

08:59.139 --> 09:00.574
It's a secret.

09:00.608 --> 09:03.010
A secret?
It's creepy is what it is.

09:03.043 --> 09:04.845
-All right, have fun...
-Have fun.

09:04.878 --> 09:06.847
...at the homeless shelter.

09:06.880 --> 09:08.782
*

09:13.120 --> 09:15.255
Be right with you, folks.

09:18.291 --> 09:20.694
Hello, little ladies.

09:20.728 --> 09:22.796
Don't you guys look beautiful?
Uh, you want to go

09:22.830 --> 09:24.965
help them over there? Yeah.

09:24.998 --> 09:28.201
Explain to me how this
is better than Linwood Baptist.

09:28.235 --> 09:31.038
Well, we just felt like,
uh, the athletic center

09:31.071 --> 09:33.406
represents a broader sample
of the 12th.

09:33.440 --> 09:36.243
Did we? Because, you know,
at this very moment,

09:36.276 --> 09:38.746
Sol Brown is handing out turkeys
over at Linwood Baptist,

09:38.779 --> 09:40.781
the biggest Thanksgiving
soup kitchen in the city,

09:40.814 --> 09:43.383
which gets photographed
every year by The Inquirer,

09:43.416 --> 09:44.718
The Telegraph,
The Philadelphia Tribune...

09:44.752 --> 09:46.419
Please stop
saying newspapers at me.

09:46.453 --> 09:48.555
We-we don't need a photo op,
you know?

09:48.588 --> 09:50.423
Randall wants to connect
with the people.

09:50.457 --> 09:52.159
He doesn't want to look
like the guy who drove in

09:52.192 --> 09:53.927
to hold a ladle
and get his picture taken.

09:53.961 --> 09:55.428
-We just want...
-I need to go to the bathroom.

09:55.462 --> 09:57.798
Oh...

09:57.831 --> 10:00.400
To not be continued.

10:00.433 --> 10:03.236
-Excuse me.
-Mm-hmm.

10:03.270 --> 10:06.173
Have we landed on a job title
for your wife?

10:06.206 --> 10:09.009
Yeah, field director. She'll
spread my message, coordinate...

10:09.042 --> 10:12.445
I'm aware what a field director
does, since I usually hire them.

10:12.479 --> 10:15.683
Randall, has your wife
ever worked on a campaign?

10:15.716 --> 10:17.284
Because I think
she needs to understand

10:17.317 --> 10:18.952
-that there's a system here.
-Hey, Jae-won.

10:18.986 --> 10:20.754
You've done an amazing job.

10:20.788 --> 10:22.422
All right?
You joining my campaign

10:22.455 --> 10:24.424
has been divine intervention.

10:24.457 --> 10:27.627
But Beth is my wife,
and she's for real

10:27.661 --> 10:30.163
and it's not open
for discussion.

10:30.197 --> 10:33.033
("Just a Friend"
by Biz Markie playing)

10:33.066 --> 10:35.002
Well, this is fun.

10:36.904 --> 10:39.673
* Oh, baby, you

10:39.707 --> 10:42.710
* You got what I need

10:42.743 --> 10:45.045
* You got everything I need

10:45.078 --> 10:47.180
* You're like medicine to me

10:47.214 --> 10:48.548
* Oh, baby...

10:48.581 --> 10:51.184
Here you go.
Happy Thanksgiving to you.

10:51.218 --> 10:53.020
They're raising my rent again.

10:53.053 --> 10:56.656
-They want me to move out.
-Of course they do.

10:56.690 --> 10:59.059
Landlords want higher income
earners to move in.

10:59.092 --> 11:02.229
* So glad you saved me, dear

11:02.262 --> 11:04.197
* Saved me, dear... *

11:04.231 --> 11:06.166
Happy Thanksgiving to you,
young man. Okay.

11:06.199 --> 11:08.301
* Things were wrong,
you made them right *

11:08.335 --> 11:11.404
* How did you do it, dear?

11:11.438 --> 11:13.540
* Do it, dear *

11:13.573 --> 11:16.910
* Oh, I'm thankful every day

11:16.944 --> 11:19.412
* Oh, that you came my way

11:19.446 --> 11:21.882
* And I hope and pray

11:21.915 --> 11:24.317
* That you never ever go away

11:24.351 --> 11:28.055
* 'Cause you, oh,
you got what I need *

11:28.088 --> 11:29.522
* Little girl...

11:29.556 --> 11:32.225
Don't be shy.
This is a growing girl.

11:32.259 --> 11:34.161
* You're like medincine to me

11:34.194 --> 11:35.662
* Oh, baby...

11:35.695 --> 11:37.230
ANNIE:
Deja, you're giving too many.

11:37.264 --> 11:39.399
The man said
only one cookie a person.

11:39.432 --> 11:41.869
Well, the man doesn't get it.

11:41.902 --> 11:43.771
-BETH: Man..

11:43.804 --> 11:46.339
None of my messages
are getting through to Kate.

11:46.373 --> 11:48.275
Mm. This reception sucks.

11:48.308 --> 11:50.110
We should put that
on our platform:

11:50.143 --> 11:51.711
fix cell phone service
in Philly.

11:51.745 --> 11:53.914
Happy Thanksgiving.

11:53.947 --> 11:56.416
* Don't ever stop them, dear

11:56.449 --> 11:59.086
* Stop them dear... *

11:59.119 --> 12:01.121
No, no. Wait, wait, hold up.

12:01.154 --> 12:02.890
Great news.
I convinced a photographer

12:02.923 --> 12:04.691
from Linwood Baptist to come
here and take some pictures.

12:04.724 --> 12:06.059
Best of both worlds, baby.

12:06.093 --> 12:07.260
-Oh, dude, that's great.
-Yeah.

12:07.294 --> 12:11.531
That's

12:11.564 --> 12:14.034
I'm sorry, guys. I just...
I don't think it's a good idea.

12:14.067 --> 12:17.104
People came here to have
a nice meal with their families,

12:17.137 --> 12:19.139
and most of them don't want
to be photographed

12:19.172 --> 12:21.608
getting a handout. You know,
Randall's whole strategy...

12:21.641 --> 12:23.143
You know, his strategy
is to get more votes

12:23.176 --> 12:24.277
than he currently has, Beth.

12:28.648 --> 12:32.786
Guys, stop.

12:32.820 --> 12:34.354
All right, I'm sorry, Jae-won.

12:41.461 --> 12:43.096
-I-I called in a favor, man.
-I know,

12:43.130 --> 12:45.665
and I'm sorry, but you should've
run it by us first.

12:45.698 --> 12:48.268
No, actually, no, because
I'm the campaign manager

12:48.301 --> 12:50.103
-and what I'm supposed to do
is get-- No, no.
-Jae-won, please.

12:50.137 --> 12:51.571
Randall, you're
making a mistake.

12:51.604 --> 12:52.806
What do you want me to do, man?

12:52.840 --> 12:54.641
I don't care if it's a mistake,

12:54.674 --> 12:56.810
she's my wife.

13:01.114 --> 13:05.618
-Yeah, um, happy Thanksgiving.
-To you and yours

13:05.652 --> 13:08.588
as well, man. Hey...

13:08.621 --> 13:10.457
Oh, man.

13:10.490 --> 13:12.392
Yeah...

13:17.664 --> 13:20.600
Ooh, a terrier!
Dad, could we go play with it?

13:20.633 --> 13:24.004
-Yeah, let's go say hi.
-Oh, yay!

13:24.037 --> 13:25.205
Hey, Randall.

13:25.238 --> 13:27.207
Yeah.

13:27.240 --> 13:29.376
I'm just curious.

13:29.409 --> 13:32.545
Of my 300 ideas
over the past few weeks,

13:32.579 --> 13:34.982
how many of them
did you really think were--

13:35.015 --> 13:36.383
What's the word you used?

13:36.416 --> 13:39.719
-Stupendous.
-Or...

13:39.752 --> 13:42.389
how many times were you just
trying to make me feel good

13:42.422 --> 13:44.191
because you thought
your recently-fired wife

13:44.224 --> 13:45.392
needed a win?

13:45.425 --> 13:48.228
Beth...

13:48.261 --> 13:52.866
Oh, man. That's what I thought.

13:52.900 --> 13:54.968
Actually, it's not
what I thought,

13:55.002 --> 13:58.872
-you know, which really sucks.

14:00.007 --> 14:02.142
-Hey.
-Oh, God.

14:02.175 --> 14:04.477
-Oh, man. We got to get home.

14:04.511 --> 14:07.180
-Come on, girls. Let's go.
-Come on.

14:07.214 --> 14:11.084
-Yeah.

